Notes for the msabramo/phpserialize fork:

Blog post: http://marc-abramowitz.com/archives/2011/10/25/phpserialize-on-python-3/

To use this fork:

* In a pip requirements file:

    -e git+git://github.com/msabramo/phpserialize.git@python3.x#egg=phpserialize

* In a tox.ini file, in the deps setting:

    https://github.com/msabramo/phpserialize/tarball/python3.x

Notes from the upstream repo below:

a port of the serialize and unserialize functions of php to python. This module
implements the python serialization interface (eg: provides dumps, loads and
similar functions).
